description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Royal Free London NHS Foundation Trust are looking to recruit an Endoscopy Decontamination Team Leader for Wednesday to Sunday 08:00 to 16:00 to work in their state of the art, reprocessing facility in Enfield EN1 1TZ which opened in June 2019.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role involves the decontamination and maintenance of all endoscopy scopes, the traceability and documentation of decontamination procedure and the reporting and returning of faulty endoscopic equipment. . You will support the supervisor with the management of the decontamination technicians on the shift. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The unit facilitates the sterilisation and decontamination of medical devices for our Trust and customers. The unit has been built with the capacity to provide services for external customers looking to outsource these services to a specialist NHS-led unit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The unit is the most modern facility, with we believe, the greatest capacity in the country for both Sterile Services and Endoscopy Reprocessing. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;There will be a numeracy and literacy screening assessment on the day prior to interview.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you would like to be part of this exciting time for our trust, then please apply.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Jason Cox&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Deputy General Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: jasoncox@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0207 794 0500 ext 54106&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
